## File Placement
- Keep Augment configs/ignores inside `augment/` (e.g., `augment/.augment.md`, `augment/.augmentignore`).
- Do **not** place data, code, or docs under `augment/`—configs only.
- Never duplicate this file; keep it only at the exact path above.

## Cleanliness Rules
- No new markdown unless explicitly required and permanently placed (follow `AGENTS.md` hard stops).
- Avoid root clutter; remove stale or duplicate Augment artifacts promptly.
- Keep links to the core docs up to date.

## Do / Don’t (Augment Codes)
- ✅ Use `augment/` for Augment configs/ignores only.
- ✅ Follow naming conventions from `AGENTS.md` (`volatility_*` vs `volume_*`; no `vol_*`).
- ✅ Reference the active plan in `.cursor/plans/` before changes.
- ❌ Don’t scatter Augment files outside `augment/` or repo guardrails.
- ❌ Don’t add data, notebooks, or code to `augment/`.
